{"author":{"id":"ae924cad0eccd510bd7c1844896b3dcc00e7daa039003bd9719a515e70528ab9"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1490992059,"nonce":"aHBKRDCobYVkhck55xk4bkycqsE=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUyMTg2MDg1OTY=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1226","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhancements for multiGPS","message":"MultiGPS is now on main. It is cutting edge binding site finder that analyzes multiple samples at once and performs differential binding analysis and motif search in one go. It can be used for analysis of ChIP-exo data out of the box. It is developed by @shaunmahony and wrapped by @gregvonkuster. \n\nBefore it is fully operational we need to make the following enhancements:\n\n- [ ] Currently one cannot use multiple experiments as inputs. This is critical as without this functionality there is no point in having multiGPS.  I have this one currently underway.\n- [ ] Currently multiGPS outputs data in a custom tab delimited format. It should really be able to output BED so it easily flows into browsers, interval operations, and so on.  This one will require work by Shaun Mahony.\n- [ ] Another nice-to-have enhancement is to create a conda a recipe for the parallel version of meme https://github.com/bioconda/bioconda-recipes/tree/master/recipes/meme.  MultiGPS can take advantage of this, so I'll see if I can find time to do it (lower priority than above).","files":null}]}